## 12. Definition of Done

Every change is complete only when all of the following are true:

- [ ] Intent restated in prose; acceptance criteria written as Given/When/Then statements.
- [ ] Every acceptance criterion has a passing, named automated test.
- [ ] All tests satisfy F.I.R.S.T.
- [ ] No function violates the size, argument-count, or abstraction-level rules.
- [ ] No class violates SRP.
- [ ] Zero duplication, zero magic numbers, zero dead code, zero commented-out code.
- [ ] Every name survives scrutiny against the naming rules.
- [ ] Public API has docstrings; internals are silent unless justified.
- [ ] Error handling uses exceptions; `null` is neither returned nor accepted across any boundary.
- [ ] Every third-party boundary is wrapped; vendor types do not leak into the domain.
- [ ] The build is one command. The tests are one command.
- [ ] Lint, formatter, and type-checker pass with zero warnings suppressed.
- [ ] New tech debt is named, documented, and filed.

---

*"Clean code always looks like it was written by someone who cares."*
